rComments: very sweet and caring and kind. but his tests are WAY TOO hard.

A nice guy but boy he screwed us over for the exam - term tests were fairly easy but the exam was 3 hours of torture, with complex calculations required in addition to the challenging material itself. Implements 'active learning' - which means he doesn't really teach but assigns problems and expects us to magically solve them with little teaching.

His lectures are great, he tests you on the stuff he actually taught and he wants you to know for the course. Exam was hard but because he made the midterms very easy. His TAs are awesome, appreciate the in-class worksheets.

Sometimes his tests are hard, like a lot of profs, but sometimes his tests aren't hard hard they are deceptively simple if you know the meaning of what you are doing but they seem too easy if you just learned one way to do a problem, so with him you have to be flexible and learn multiple ways of doing a problem and understand how things are defined
Gr8 for the ones want to pursure in pure math. Teaches you how to approach the problems very accurately
A lot of abstract concepts but not fully explained, neither from text book nor professor. Don't take this course if you have choice.

Test 1 average was 38, so he had to do this "the total number of available points will be reduced to 13 from 15". So the average has increased to 44. Marking took forever. I got a grade for an assignment after a month it was due. This was the worst prof I've ever had(it's my 4th year).
I love the way he explains concepts, he really clarifies them for me and going to class is so much fun

Alex is an awesome prof. He tries to push his students in understanding the concepts, and that makes his tests hard. I had him for mat135 and mat223, and he was a great. I did not like the mat223 course content, and I found it difficult. However, that does not make him a bad prof. He just tries to test the material taught; and thats the point.
Test 2 was difficult but was made up for w/ easy tests 1 and 3. Exam was fair
the ave of midterm of this course (mat 344) is 36.9%. assignment's and quiz's mark is Low. Also quiz is very difficult. Do not take his course
Just amazing proff!! Loved his lectures, way of explaining, posting of the lecture notes online, and his overall caring attitude!! Hands down one of the best professors I've ever had!!
Do not take his any course.
He's a funny guy, but he's kind of nervous outside of lecture. Pretty transparent.
You do not need to solve practice midterm that he gives you before the midterm. It is nothing similar to the actual midterm test. lol be aware

To be honest, this prof is a good man and I like him because he respects all students while he is teaching. But his lecture is way too off for his assignments and quiz. like, He explained like 1+1 in the class and expect you to solve things like 7^3/(7). He will be perfect if we can actually expect what is going to come on quizzes and the tests.

Alex is amazing. Super funny and caring guy. He knows his stuff and will do his best to make the lecture fun by cracking jokes here and there. Gives amazing examples that sometimes show up on tests. Online assignments are 10% and are so easy. Tests weren't bad and tutorials were really helpful. You'll be lost if you skip a lecture. Overall, amazing
great

Amazing prof! Everyone loves him. Makes concepts very clear. Helpful outside of classroom. But the workload is too much. Quizzes are difficult. Lots lots lots of homework and the problems are challenging. I wish I wasn't taking full course load so I could spend more time studying for his class. Recommend to those who doesn't have heavy course load.

This course is really hard and intensive. You have to think a lot to find out what the answer of the problem should be, and the assignments are really difficult and challenging. However, Alex is an amazing prof, he is really helpful, caring, and respected. He responds to any email questions really quick, and always willing to help during office hrs

Very work intensive and difficult. The assignments he gives out are long and challenging. Even so, he is very supportive. He will respond to any email questions within a few hours, and he is very helpful during office hours. I was impressed with the respect he had for students.
Great and so smart prof for his age. he has successful future
immaculate teacher
Excellent and caring professor. Good looking and funny as well. Just be on top of work and be consistent and you should be good
Great prof would recommend to take him. Go for his office hours, very helpful, patient and understanding
He make this course very hard this year.

Sometimes his assignments can be really hard to understand.  This class was okay as he did not really teach that much, students were expected to read the textbook, solve questions and present in the class.
Good prof. But, need to practice a lot for homework and tests. Overall, he is a very good teacher.

Alex is a best prof!!!! He is so nice and really handsome. He always makes the class to be fun, and you will love being in his class, never feel boring or sleepy. His office hours are also really helpful if you go and talk to him.

Alex is a pretty nice person and teacher. He is teaching with very clear mind and teaches with clear steps. He is very pleased that you have questions and ask him.  He is also a funny guy. You won't feel boring in his classes handsome teacher XD

I really love Alex!!! He is the best math prof I ever had. Hot and has a great sense of humor. His lectures are fun and good to be in, and one of the reason that make me come to class is because of him lol.. definitely take courses with him again
